The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 21 April is 271,994 (31,348.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 16 April, there were 2,739 new confirmed cases (315.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 09 April, there were 4,020 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 32% (1,281 fewer cases).
